Package com.googlecode.cqengine.index.support

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CloseableIterable<T>  
    CloseableIterator<T>  
    Factory<T>
    A generic factory for an object of type T.
    KeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,O>
    Implemented by indexes which support key statistics and are attribute-centric.
    KeyStatisticsIndex<A,O>
    An index which allows the set of distinct keys to be queried, and which can return statistics on the number of objects stored in the buckets for each key.
    ResourceIndex
    A marker interface which indexes may implement to signal that they open resources which should be closed after each request is processed.
    SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>
    Implemented by indexes which support sorted key statistics and are attribute-centric.
    SortedKeyStatisticsIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>
    An index which allows the set of distinct keys to be queried in sorted order, and which can return statistics on the number of objects stored for each key.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractAttributeIndex<A,O>
    A skeleton implementation of an index which implements the Index.supportsQuery(Query) method, based on a set of queries supported by a subclass supplied to the constructor.
    AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex<A,O,MapType extends ConcurrentMap<A,StoredResultSet<O>>>
    An abstract implementation of an index backed by a ConcurrentMap, where the exact map implementation is provided by a factory supplied to the constructor.
    CloseableQueryResources
    A QueryOption that allows to keep track of query resources that need to be closed.
    The engine will then make sure that, when the outer result-set close method is called, all the resources are closed.
    CloseableSet
    Utility class to facilitate the addition of ResultSet's resources in the QueryOptions' CloseableQueryResources.
    DefaultConcurrentSetFactory<O>
    Creates a concurrent implementation of a Set, based on ConcurrentHashMap.
    LazyCloseableIterator<T>  
    UnmodifiableNavigableSet<E>
    A read-only view of a NavigableSet.
